  "prompt": "Who whave my number on watsapp?",
  "response": "WhatsApp doesn't provide a direct feature that tells you exactly who has your number saved in their contacts. However, there are a few indirect ways you might get an idea:\n\n*   **WhatsApp Groups:** If someone who isn't in your contacts adds you to a WhatsApp group, it's a strong indication they have your number saved.\n*   **\"View Once\" Images/Videos:** If you send a \"view once\" image or video to all your contacts, you could then contact each person in your contact list to see if they viewed it. Anyone who says they didn't view it and who you weren't expecting to view it might have you in their contacts, but you aren't in theirs.\n*   **Privacy Settings:** You can use WhatsApp's privacy settings to control who can see your profile picture, last seen status, about information, and status updates. If you set these to \"My Contacts,\" only people who have your number saved in their contacts will be able to see them. You won't know exactly *who* has your number, but you'll know if someone who isn't in your contacts tries to view your profile information.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Data Privacy:** Keep in mind that any attempts to figure out who has your number might not be foolproof and could potentially violate WhatsApp's terms of service or raise privacy concerns for others.\n*   **Legitimate Use:** It's important to have a legitimate reason for wanting to know who has your number. If you're concerned about unwanted contact or harassment, it's best to block the number or report it to WhatsApp.",
